# Environment
.env
*.env

# Logs
logs/
*.log

# Vector DBs / embeddings
chroma/
vectordb/
# derived RAG store cache (vectors.json/index.json/summaries.json) — rebuilt by sync()
# (comment on its own line: git treats a trailing inline comment as part of the pattern)
database/cache/

# Runtime SQLite store (checkpoints + trace runs/events/llm_calls) — churns every turn, recreated
# on first run; tracking it produced constant binary diffs in git status. Sidecars appear in WAL mode.
database/db.sqlite
database/db.sqlite-wal
database/db.sqlite-shm

# First-run / first-use sentinels — runtime state written on first launch/use; not source.
database/.setup_done
database/.gate_seen
database/.hint_*

# User data that must survive /update (git pull): saved sessions (named /save files + the
# /resume autosave slot), the persisted policy decisions (/policy risk --save + /policy allow),
# the /undo snapshots, and user-defined slash-command templates.
# Ignoring the whole paths means a future tracked file can never collide with a user's local
# one and break the ff-only pull — user-generated artifacts live ONLY in ignored paths.
# (database/recipes/ kept ignored for installs that predate the plan-recipes cut.)
database/sessions/
database/permissions.json
database/snapshots/
database/recipes/
database/commands/
# ed25519 audit-signing PRIVATE key — must never be committed. (Comment on its own line: git
# treats a trailing inline comment as part of the pattern, which would match NOTHING.)
database/signing_key.json
# durable cross-session egress audit log (also matched by *.log above; kept explicit)
database/egress.log

# Model cache
models/
ollama/

# Build
dist/
build/

# Python bytecode cache (never track — caused binary merge conflicts pre-consolidation)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

.vscode

CLAUDE.md

USER.md

CONSOLIDATION.md

# Claude/dev-only working docs — not shipped to installers. documentation.md is the local
# detailed feature reference + changelog (see CLAUDE.md "Documentation maintenance"). The other
# three were deleted (historical build log / refactor plan / vision doc); their patterns stay so
# a restored copy is never accidentally tracked.
NOTES.md
RESTRUCTURE.md
SATURDAY_MVP_PLAN.md
documentation.md
repo-overview.md
production-readiness.md

# Generated dev artifacts: benchmark result dumps (benchmarks/*.json) and Mermaid/PNG graph
# exports (graphs/). diag.log is already covered by *.log above; this catches the rest.
logging/

# Dogfooding workspace files, durable memory, and the derived .manifest.md summaries — all
# runtime/test data, recreated as needed on first run (files.py mkdir), so users don't inherit
# our local files. The documents/ corpus ships with exactly one seeded doc: welcome-to-saturn.md
# gives a fresh install a working knowledge base + onboarding; everything else in documents/
# (your ingested files, the derived .manifest.md) stays ignored.
database/documents/*
!database/documents/welcome-to-saturn.md
database/workspace/
database/memory/